scale2x
------------------------------------------
Scale2x, Scale3x and Scale4x are real-time graphics effects able to increase
the size of small bitmaps guessing the missing pixels without blurring the
images.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.4.3-1
  libpng16-1.6.37-1
  zlib0-1.2.13-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.39-1
  cygport-0.35.5-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libpng-devel-1.6.37-1
  make-4.4-1
  zlib-devel-1.2.13-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/amadvance/scale2x

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/amadvance/scale2x/archive/refs/tags/v4.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack scale2x-4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./scale2x-4.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/scale2x-4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/scale2x-4.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(scale2x)
  /usr/bin/scalerx.exe
  /usr/bin/scalex.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/scale2x.README
  /usr/share/doc/scale2x/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/scale2x/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/scale2x/HISTORY
  /usr/share/doc/scale2x/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/scalerx.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/scalex.1.gz

